article.headline: Air Force 59, Prairie View 46
article.story: BERKELEY, Calif. (AP) -- Tim Keller scored 13 of his 16 points in the second half to lead Air Force to a 59-46 victory over Prairie View in the opener of the Golden Bear Classic on Saturday night. Air Force (5-2) led 31-27 in the second half before going on a 15-4 run. Keller completed the run with back-to-back 3-pointers that gave Air Force a 46-31 lead with 7:29 to play. Kevin Cooper had 20 points for Prairie View (0-8). Jacob Burtschi had 11 points and six rebounds for Air Force, and hit a 3-pointer during the crucial second-half run. Antoine Hood also had 11 points for the Falcons. Air Force overcame a 35-21 Prairie View rebounding edge. Air Force was 11-of-29 on 3-pointers.
